## Setup Instructions

### Local Development

1. Clone this repository to your local machine:
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/wedding-website.git
   ```

2. Open the files in your favorite code editor.

3. To preview the site locally, you can use any simple web server. For example, with Python:
   ```
   # Python 3
   python -m http.server
   
   # Python 2
   python -m SimpleHTTPServer
   ```

4. Visit `http://localhost:8000` in your browser to view the site.

### Customization

#### Google Form Integration

To set up the RSVP page with your Google Form:

1. Create a Google Form for your RSVP responses in Google Drive.
2. Click the "Send" button and select the embed option (</> icon).
3. Copy the provided iframe code.
4. Open `rsvp.html` and replace the iframe in the `.google-form` div with your copied code.

#### Content Customization

- Update text content in each HTML file to match your wedding details.
- Replace placeholder images with your own photos.
- Customize colors by editing the CSS variables in the `:root` section of `style.css`.

## Deployment on GitHub Pages

1. Create a new repository on GitHub.

2. Initialize your local repository and push to GitHub:
   ```
   git init
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial commit"
   git branch -M main
   git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/wedding-website.git
   git push -u origin main
   ```

3. Configure GitHub Pages:
   - Go to your repository settings on GitHub
   - Scroll down to the "GitHub Pages" section
   - Select the "main" branch as the source
   - Save the settings

4. Your site will be published at `https://yourusername.github.io/wedding-website/`

